edit: Michael T. Osterholm is a public health scientist and a biosecurity and infectious disease expert in the United States. Joe Rogan had him on his episode for his podcast and they discussed coronavirus. Osterholm is saying this is going to be 6-12 month issue that impacts older people and those with underlying health issues such as obesity. He predicted/studied this type of scenario playing out, how it would impact supply chain and wrote about it in his book. He doesn't believe its bio-weaponized and discredits other myths of using saunas, probiotics, etc to fight it. Osterholm also states that washing your hands and not touching your face hasn't been captured as affective prevention but that White House officials and public want something to be able to do. Furthermore, he mentioned that saying that the risk is low is a false assertion. Still going through the video but it's very informative.

